				\begin{document}$$D=\frac{K\lambda }{FWHM\,\cos \,\theta }$$\end{document}where, D is the averaged dimension of crystallites; K is the Scherrer constant, an arbitrary value that falls in the range 0.87–1.0 (usually assumed to be 0.9); λ is the wavelength of X-ray; and FWHM is pure diffraction broadening of a peak at half height, due to crystallite dimensions located at 2θ.

